'''''Modern Healthcare''''' is a weekly, 70,037-circulation business publication targeting executives in the [[healthcare]] industry.  It is an independent American publisher of national and regional healthcare news.  

The publication is also known for providing statistical rankings,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.commonwealthfund.org/Content/Surveys/2007/The-Commonwealth-Fund--Modern-Healthcare--Health-Care-Opinion-Leaders-Survey--Transparency-of-Health.aspx | title=The Commonwealth Fund/"Modern Healthcare" Health Care Opinion Leaders Survey: Transparency of Health Care Quality and Price Information in the United States | The Commonwealth Fund, accessdate=2007-10}}</ref> competitive insight, and practical information on topics such as [[information technology]], federal and state legislation, [[Medicare (United States)|Medicare]]/[[Medicaid]], [[finance]], access to capital, [[reimbursement]], [[investing]], [[supply chain]], [[materials management]], [[strategic planning]], [[governance]], [[managed care]], [[insurers]], EHRs,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://ehrdecisions.com/2009/05/28/modern-healthcare-mark-leavitt-discusses-stimulus/ | title=Modern Healthcare: Mark Leavitt discusses stimulus | EHR Decisions, accessdate=2009-05-28}}</ref> [[patient safety]], quality, outpatient care,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://blog.aahomecare.org/2009/04/modern-healthcare-reports-on-hme.html | title=Modern Healthcare Reports on HME Communities Request to Rescind Bidding Rule  | American Association for Homecare,  accessdate=2009-04-14}}</ref> [[rural health]], [[construction]], [[Human resources|staffing]], legal affairs and international healthcare. 

Modern Healthcare organizes several events, including its annual Health Care Hall of Fame<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mayoclinic.org/news2009-rst/5186.html | title=Mayo Brothers to be Inducted into Healthcare Hall of Fame | Mayo Clinic, accessdate=2009-02-16}}</ref> awards <ref>{{cite news | url=http://twincities.bizjournals.com/twincities/stories/2009/02/16/daily13.html | title=Mayo brothers named to Health Care Hall of Fame | Minneapolis Business Journal, accessdate=2009-02-16 | first=John | last=Vomhof Jr | date=2009-02-16}}</ref> dinner and The 100 Most Powerful People in Healthcare<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.bizjournals.com/louisville/stories/2008/08/25/daily46.html | title=Diaz, McCallister named to Modern Healthcareâ€™s '100 most powerful'  | Business First, accessdate=2008-08-29 | date=2008-08-29}}</ref> list <ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-183635244.html | title=Modern Healthcare Names Steve Case Most Powerful Person in Healthcare | High Beam Research, accessdate=2008-08-25}}</ref>

== Publication history ==
''Modern Healthcare'' was established in 1976 and is based in Chicago, Ill.  ''Modern Healthcare'' is owned and published by Detroit-based [[Crain Communications Inc.]].  

The publication launched a web site in 1998 and offers 4 daily e-mail newsletters.

